              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "NGEN"
                ],
                "institute": "3CPRNPC"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " K-400 neutron generator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "About 9 gram of Tb2O3 powder of natural isotopic",
                "composition (>99.99% pure) was pressed at 10 ton/cm2,",
                "and a pellet, 0.2 cm thick and 2.0 cm in diameter was",
                "obtained. The samples in each group were sandwiched",
                "between two Nb or Al foils."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The crystal geometry is 70.1 x 72.3 mm in",
                "diameter and length. The relative efficiency is about",
                "68%, and energy resolution is 1.69 keV at 1332 keV",
                "gamma ray from Co-60."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The Au-Si surface barrier detector used in",
                "135 degree accompanying alpha particle tube was at a",
                "distance of 110 cm from the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Irradiation of the samples was lasted about",
                "13 hours with a yield around 2E10 to 3E10 n/s, and",
                "cooled for around 5.5 to 78 hours. The groups of",
                "samples were placed at 0deg., 90deg. or 135deg.",
                "angles relative to the beam direction and centered",
                "about the T-Mo target at distances of around 4 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
